  "lore": {
    "description": "A compact, prolific pepper with thick walls and moderate heat — the backbone of salsas and pickled pepper rings worldwide.",
    "origin": "Xalapa (Jalapa), Veracruz, Mexico",
    "fun_fact": "The characteristic white 'corking' lines on a jalapeño's skin are stress marks — and many chili heads prize heavily corked peppers as having more concentrated heat.",
